# create-blit386 CLAUDE Is Canonical

- Treat `CLAUDE.md` at the repository root as canonical for work in this repo.
- Follow its monorepo layout, scaffold conventions, and command set.
- Generated games default to JavaScript; a TypeScript layer (`templates/ts/`, opt-in via the wizard or
  `npm create blit386 ... --ts`) is also supported. Both ship beginner-friendly comments; do not apply library-only
  TypeScript conventions (no `any` bans, named-export rules, etc.) to generated game files.
- Public engine API names in generated games must match sibling repo `blit386` (`BT.isDown`, `isOverlayEnabled`, etc.).
- Use repo commands exactly as documented in `CLAUDE.md` (`pnpm run preflight`, not bare `pnpm preflight`).
